uch every major goal. The bigger, more powerful ship with the new Raptor en=
gines soared to space, deployed its mock Starlink satellites, survived the =
fiery re-entry, and pulled off a controlled splashdown in the Indian Ocean.=
 </p><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">Even with the usual =E2=80=9Cfiery finish=
=E2=80=9D after landing (normal for these test flights), Elon called it an =
=E2=80=9Cepic first Starship V3 launch &amp; landing.=E2=80=9D This was the=
 cleanest, most capable test yet =E2=80=94 huge step toward full reusabilit=
y. Why investors should care: With the SpaceX IPO now just 20 days away, to=
day=E2=80=99s success is perfect timing. It shows the company is moving fas=
t on the tech that will power Starlink=E2=80=99s next phase and future Mars=
 missions. Momentum is clearly building! </p><p></p></div></td></tr>
